info:
Job Description：

1. Master at least one programming languages: Python, C++;
2. Master at least one Python Web Framework: FastAPI, Flask;
3. Master at least one AI Framework: Scikit-Learn, PyTorch, TensorFlow
4. Master at least one kind of AI models: vision models, time-series models;
5. Master basic programming skills: Docker, VSCode, SSH, Development on Linux; JSON and YAML;
6. Priority will be given to those with data cleaning experience;
7. Priority will be given to those with Nvidia CUDA programming, Nvidia TAO;
8. Priority will be given to those with Darts, SKTime, statsmodels;
9. Priority will be given to those who have completed an internship of 4 months or longer.
10. Second year graduate students and above; Doctoral students

Responsibilities
1.	Support in daily operations within Service and Quality team;
2.	Support in administrative tasks for Director After Sales Service and Quality;
3.	Overall projects support in 4 projects regarding RTM, Battery Coding & Tracking, recycling as well as warranty and audit regulations;
4.	Support in process definitions and preparation of PowerPoint presentations;
5.	Support in coordination and consolidation of sub-team assignments.

Requirements
1.	Pursuing a Bachelor or Master degree, solid knowledge in Automotive, Engineering, Project Management or Finance areas;
2.	Excellent intercultural and communication skills, proactive attitude, diligent. stress resistant and willing to learn;
3.	Familiar with MS Office (word, excel, PowerPoint)
4.	Familiar with Data Processing Tool (Tableau, Power BI, etc.);
5.	Fluent in both oral and written English;
6.	Committed and available to work at least 4 days a week for 6 months;

Responsibilities
1. Support Specialist Training Coordination and Development for the notification delivery to specific dealers in training projects
2.Support Senior Specialist Training Planning and Reporting for the notification delivery to specific dealers for cost recharge & dealer monitoring related tasks if needed
3. Support the dealer feedback collection in different training projects
4. Responsible for the operation in PALMS 2.0 system for the cancellation, replacement and other daily attendees change according to the task released by Specialist Training Coordination and Development
5. Responsible for the half-yearly training module and session opening in PALMS 2.0 system according to the training object list and planned half-year calendar
6. Support the whole training planning process incl. dealer feedback collection and data consolidation
7. Support the daily operation for the local platforms (e.g Porsche Mobile Academy and other platforms) according to the need from Senior Specialist Training Systems and Methods

Requirements
1. Bachelor degree or above;
2. Internship experience in the automotive industry or other luxury brands as a plus;
3. Fluent in both oral and written English;
4. Good command of MS Office softwares;
5. Excellent intercultural and communication skills, proactive attitude, diligent, stress resistant and willing to learn;
6. Committed and available to work at least 5 days a week;
7. Internship period at least 6 months.
